dead—bolt from the inside.

03:24.038 --> 03:25.198
No one got in here to take her.

03:25.331 --> 03:27.697
Harper couldn't have done this.

03:27.833 --> 03:29.994
Ma'am, some people
have special abilities

03:30.127 --> 03:31.207
that they can't control.

03:31.337 --> 03:33.703
That make them do things
they can't normally do.

03:33.839 --> 03:36.296
You're talking about the troubles.

03:36.425 --> 03:38.666
We don't have those in our family.

03:38.803 --> 03:41.169
Do you have some recent photos
of Harper?

03:45.267 --> 03:46.723
A troubled four—year—old?

03:46.852 --> 03:48.558
Yeah, I know.

03:50.689 --> 03:53.351
We need Audrey back now.

03:53.484 --> 03:55.395
All right, William...

03:55.528 --> 03:57.735
What is this barn
that I'm supposedly in?

03:57.863 --> 04:00.445
lt's —— it's a space
between two worlds,

04:00.574 --> 04:01.825
and it's been badly damaged.

04:01.951 --> 04:04.237
If you don't leave soon,
you will die.

04:04.370 --> 04:05.735
You know what?
That's easy for you to say,

04:05.871 --> 04:07.122
'cause the last time
I tried to leave,

04:07.248 --> 04:09.239
| just walked out that door
and came straight back in.

04:09.375 --> 04:11.866
You have to find the real door,
the door that leads back to Haven.

04:12.002 --> 04:12.866
Mm.

04:13.629 --> 04:16.245
