11:42.286 --> 11:46.996
You're more important than you know,
and your friends need you.

11:48.125 --> 11:49.865
What else did Jennifer hear?

11:50.002 --> 11:52.084
Just that Audrey's in the barn
and she's looking for a door.

11:52.212 --> 11:53.452
A door?

11:53.589 --> 11:56.422
Duke and Jennifer are on it.
I need you in the archives.

11:56.550 --> 12:00.213
We think this 10—year—old boy
is kidnapping the missing children.

12:02.681 --> 12:04.046
What's wrong with his teeth?

12:04.182 --> 12:05.763
That's what I want you to find out.

12:05.893 --> 12:07.599
I got to get to the brambles.

12:07.728 --> 12:09.184
They were seen headed that way.

12:14.234 --> 12:15.223
Brambles are dangerous

12:15.360 --> 12:18.067
so stay in close visual contact
with each other.

12:18.196 --> 12:20.903
If you find the kids, wrap them up
in the blankets right away.

12:21.033 --> 12:21.988
Get them warm.

12:22.117 --> 12:24.950
They're facing serious risk
of hypothermia.

12:25.078 --> 12:26.454
Let's go.

12:31.668 --> 12:33.875
Detective Wuornos?
l'm Carmen Brock.

12:34.004 --> 12:35.414
I'm the principal of Sunnyside.

12:35.547 --> 12:38.414
We actually organized
the, uh —— the search.

12:38.550 --> 12:41.417
Oh, great.
Uh, did you ——

12:43.722 --> 12:46.213
Do any of your families
have older brothers,

12:46.350 --> 12:47.806
like 10 years old?

12:47.935 --> 12:50.927
Yeah, lots of them do.

12:51.063 --> 12:52.018
VVhy?

12:52.147 --> 12:53.603
I'll need a list.

12:53.732 --> 12:56.018
But cover your sector first.

12:56.151 --> 12:57.482
We need to find those kids.

12:57.611 --> 12:59.192
Okay.

13:00.530 --> 13:02.145
Okay.

13:02.824 --> 13:04.951
[Dialing cell phone]

13:05.077 --> 13:07.864
