13:13.377 --> 13:15.083
...fantastic.

13:16.171 --> 13:18.412
Yeah, we've charged her chi,
aligned her chakras.

13:18.548 --> 13:21.255
Now we're just flushing her brain
with blood.

13:21.385 --> 13:22.716
I don't think this is working.

13:22.844 --> 13:25.221
My sinuses are exploding.

13:25.347 --> 13:26.052
I'm coming over.

13:26.181 --> 13:29.093
No,no,no,no,no.
Could you just hang on a second?

13:29.226 --> 13:31.012
You are doing great.

13:31.144 --> 13:33.226
Just...keep hanging.

13:35.315 --> 13:36.600
Hey, Nathan, you come here,

13:36.733 --> 13:38.143
bring some nails
for Audrey's coffin

13:38.276 --> 13:40.892
because having you here is
the last thing that Jennifer needs.

13:41.029 --> 13:42.735
Well, your plan isn't working.

13:42.864 --> 13:43.649
Man, what did you think ——

13:43.782 --> 13:45.397
l was gonna turn her into a yogi
in half a day?

13:45.534 --> 13:47.195
Then what the hell is your plan?

13:47.327 --> 13:48.157
Here '3 an analogy.

13:48.286 --> 13:50.948
Jennifer's at the free—throw line,
one second left in the big game.

13:51.081 --> 13:53.163
Now, if she thinks about it,
she chokes.

13:53.291 --> 13:56.454
So I am trying to distract her
from the pressure,

13:56.586 --> 13:59.248
make her think about anything else
except what she has to do

13:59.381 --> 14:01.372
so she opens up her mind.

14:01.508 --> 14:03.965
And she starts to hear.

14:04.094 --> 14:05.300
Smart.

14:05.429 --> 14:07.420
Yes, it is.

14:07.556 --> 14:08.841
[Cell phone beeps]

14:08.974 --> 14:10.089
Okay!

14:11.393 --> 14:12.724
[Cell phone beeps]

14:17.733 --> 14:19.348
Audrey's still in that barn?

14:21.361 --> 14:22.476
Then what are you doing out here?

14:22.612 --> 14:24.864
Because I've got missing children,
Jordan.

14:24.990 --> 14:27.982
Guard's out in force to find them.

14:28.118 --> 14:30.325
We're getting used
to cleaning up your messes.

14:30.454 --> 14:32.115
17.

14:33.457 --> 14:35.823
—What?
—17.

14:35.959 --> 14:38.371
That's how many people have died
because of the troubles

14:38.503 --> 14:39.879
since I shot Howard.

14:40.005 --> 14:41.836
These two kids die,
that's 19 ——

14:41.965 --> 14:43.956
Lives, Jordan, not just messes.

14:44.092 --> 14:47.084
And I think about them
with every breath I take.

14:47.220 --> 14:49.802
So you know what?
I will find Audrey.

14:49.931 --> 14:53.298
She will kill me.
The troubles will end.

14:53.852 --> 14:55.217
And then I won't have
to think anymore

14:55.353 --> 14:57.765
about all the pain
that I've caused this town.

14:59.191 --> 15:00.226
[Running footsteps approaching]

15:00.358 --> 15:02.815
—We found footprints.
—Let's go.

15:07.616 --> 15:09.857
Two small sets are Harper and Kent.

15:09.993 --> 15:13.281
Then there are bigger prints ——
barefoot, all of them.

15:13.413 --> 15:14.994
I think we're looking
at four kidnappers.

15:15.123 --> 15:17.205
Four troubled 10—year—olds?

15:17.334 --> 15:19.416
And look closely at the toes.

15:22.756 --> 15:25.088
Are those claw marks?

15:31.640 --> 15:32.880
Where have you been?

15:33.016 --> 15:35.678
I've been to the archives
and found what the police need

15:35.811 --> 15:37.051
while you've been ——

15:37.187 --> 15:39.269
Where have you been?

15:39.397 --> 15:41.012
The room.

15:41.691 --> 15:42.555
I did some reading.

15:42.692 --> 15:43.943
Oh, put that away.

15:46.863 --> 15:48.524
It's the door, Vince,

15:48.657 --> 15:50.648
the one that Audrey's
supposed to come out of.

15:50.784 --> 15:52.274
—What about it?
—It bothers me.

15:52.410 --> 15:53.570
—lt bothers you?
—Yeah.

15:53.703 --> 15:55.785
What doesn't bother you, Dave ——

15:55.914 --> 15:59.327
loud music, starchy collars,
Mrs. Perlmutter's dog?

15:59.459 --> 16:01.745
—Skittles is yappy.
—I rest my case.

16:02.462 --> 16:03.963
Nathan.

16:04.089 --> 16:07.001
Can we make this quick, guys?
I got to get back to the search.

16:07.134 --> 16:09.591
The brambles turned up nothing,
and we're running out of time.

16:09.719 --> 16:12.552
Yes, well, many cultures have tales

16:12.681 --> 16:14.967
of childlike creatures
that steal children.

16:15.100 --> 16:18.513
We've seen before where myths
are explanations for the troubles.

16:18.645 --> 16:20.852
The claws are specific, though,

16:20.981 --> 16:24.064
to an Afro—Caribbean legend
called "Douen".

16:25.026 --> 16:27.768
Douens have clawed feet
and clawed hands.

16:27.904 --> 16:31.613
Their laugh enchants children
to run away from their parents

16:31.741 --> 16:33.572
and go deep into the wilderness.

16:38.915 --> 16:41.406
That's what we're dealing with.

16:42.043 --> 16:44.580
So someone's trouble
is creating these creatures.

16:44.713 --> 16:45.247
Yeah.

16:45.380 --> 16:46.495
Now, unfortunately,

16:46.631 --> 16:48.792
news of the missing children
has spread all over town.

16:48.925 --> 16:52.463
Every parent in Haven
has their kids locked up tight.

16:52.596 --> 16:54.757
Well, that might not be enough.

16:54.890 --> 16:58.382
It says here Douens
are masters of deception.

16:58.518 --> 17:02.511
They can steal away
even the most protected child.

17:05.275 --> 17:07.732
Why can't I go outside and play?

17:07.861 --> 17:09.852
Because I said so.

17:13.074 --> 17:14.814
You can play race car if you want.

17:14.951 --> 17:15.781
Yeah!

17:22.542 --> 17:24.203
I'm gonna go double—check
the alarm system.

17:24.336 --> 17:25.951
You stay here.

17:26.087 --> 17:29.625
[Continues imitating
car motor revving]

17:30.842 --> 17:34.300
[Child giggling]

17:37.891 --> 17:40.758
Ben, what are you doing up there?

17:40.894 --> 17:42.885
[Giggling continues]

17:44.147 --> 17:46.604
[Beeping, computer voice]
Ben's window open.

17:46.733 --> 17:47.893
Ben's window closed.

17:48.026 --> 17:51.063
Ben, stop playing with the window!

17:51.780 --> 17:53.486
[Sighs]

18:02.374 --> 18:03.989
Ben?

18:11.716 --> 18:14.002
Ben!

18:14.469 --> 18:16.380
No, no!

18:16.513 --> 18:19.004
Masters of deception.

18:21.309 --> 18:22.424
All kinds.

18:22.560 --> 18:24.972
Douens are particularly good
at misleading search parties.

18:25.105 --> 18:26.936
Their victims are never found.

18:27.065 --> 18:29.898
But if they're not in the brambles ——

18:30.026 --> 18:31.357
They could be anywhere.

18:36.658 --> 18:38.819
[Giggling]

18:43.206 --> 18:45.743
[Giggling continues]

18:52.507 --> 18:54.589
I thought I did everything I could.

18:55.176 --> 18:58.634
I kept him inside.
l—l set the alarm.

18:58.763 --> 19:00.799
This isn't your fault, Valerie.

19:00.932 --> 19:03.139
Please excuse me.

19:03.727 --> 19:05.058
[Sobbing]

19:05.186 --> 19:06.801
Masters of deception...

19:06.938 --> 19:09.395
Which basically means
we don't have any idea

19:09.524 --> 19:10.479
where to look for these kids.

19:10.608 --> 19:13.315
They lure their victims
into the wilderness,

19:13.445 --> 19:16.232
and then they're never found again.

19:16.364 --> 19:18.446
There's a lot of wilderness
around Haven.

19:18.575 --> 19:21.157
And easy for a kid to die
with this cold front.

19:21.286 --> 19:22.492
We have to find whose trouble

19:22.620 --> 19:24.281
created the Douens
in the first place,

19:24.414 --> 19:26.279
and hopefully
that narrows the search.

19:26.416 --> 19:28.498
What connects Ben
to Harper and Kent?

19:28.626 --> 19:30.082
Ben doesn't even go to preschool.

19:30.211 --> 19:31.917
Who knows all three kids?

19:32.047 --> 19:34.459
The Douens targeted
these particular children.

19:34.591 --> 19:36.582
Uh, babysitter maybe,

19:36.718 --> 19:38.925
Uh, Uh, piano teacher ——
that sort of thing?

19:39.054 --> 19:40.840
An art teacher.

19:40.972 --> 19:42.633
Ben likes to paint.

19:42.766 --> 19:46.008
Ben likes to give his art
to people he loves as presents,

19:46.144 --> 19:48.135
but I'm his art teacher.

19:53.693 --> 19:55.433
That one's for his aunt.

19:57.572 --> 20:00.780
Ant. Car. Man.

20:01.743 --> 20:04.280
To Aunt Carmen.

20:04.412 --> 20:07.449
ls Ben's aunt Carmen Brock,
principal of Sunnyside preschool?

20:07.582 --> 20:09.698
She's my sister.

20:09.834 --> 20:11.415
Ben loves her.

20:17.175 --> 20:20.008
[Exhales]

20:23.640 --> 20:24.846
[Cheers]

20:24.974 --> 20:28.216
Take that, Duke—sama—rama.
Drink.

20:28.353 --> 20:30.389
[Clears throat]
Kanpai.

20:30.522 --> 20:31.887
[Giggles]
Okay, now, this ——

20:32.023 --> 20:33.308
This I can do.

20:34.275 --> 20:36.687
Okay.
[Clears throat]

20:36.820 --> 20:38.060
Ah.

20:39.823 --> 20:40.903
Here we go.

20:41.658 --> 20:43.899
Your friends need you.

20:44.452 --> 20:45.908
Duke”.

20:46.037 --> 20:48.369
I can hear.

20:48.498 --> 20:49.908
Your friends are searching
for you right now.

20:50.041 --> 20:51.372
It means one of them is special.

20:51.501 --> 20:53.082
They have a connection to the barn.

20:53.211 --> 20:55.202
My friends.
Oh, hey, friend!

20:55.338 --> 20:57.829
Can you help me find this door
I'm supposed to find?

20:57.966 --> 21:00.378
They can't help you with your door.
They have their own to find.

21:00.510 --> 21:02.501
Wait. Stop. Wait.
You have two doors now?

21:02.637 --> 21:05.219
Yes. One that you must open,
and one that they must open.

21:05.348 --> 21:07.885
Oh, like adjoining motel rooms?

21:08.017 --> 21:11.885
Yes, both have to be open
for you to escape and survive.

21:12.021 --> 21:14.398
I knew someone would be looking.

21:14.524 --> 21:16.856
You always have friends.

21:16.985 --> 21:19.192
It's part of who you are.

21:21.030 --> 21:22.566
We have to find a door.

21:24.200 --> 21:25.781
—|'m sorry. What?
—Shh.

21:25.910 --> 21:26.660
l have to listen.

21:26.786 --> 21:27.992
[Echoing]
...to listen

21:28.121 --> 21:30.157
Listening ——
That's not a bad idea.

21:30.290 --> 21:32.155
Use your other senses.
Maybe that can help you.

21:32.292 --> 21:35.659
Okay, so now you want me
to hear a door.

21:35.795 --> 21:39.413
Would that be the strangest thing
I've asked you to do?

21:40.884 --> 21:42.715
[Sighs]

21:45.388 --> 21:47.128
[Foghorn blows]

21:47.265 --> 21:49.301
Ah! I lost it.
There's a foghorn out there.

21:49.434 --> 21:50.514
Look, just ignore it.

21:50.643 --> 21:52.304
Tell me more about this door
we need to find.

21:52.437 --> 21:55.304
She finds one, and we find one.

21:55.440 --> 21:58.182
If we fail, she dies.

21:59.277 --> 22:00.608
A door to what?

22:00.737 --> 22:02.568
I'm not sure.

22:04.282 --> 22:05.692
Adjoining motel rooms?

22:05.825 --> 22:07.781
—|'m sorry?
—Not that.

22:07.911 --> 22:09.242
Shh!

22:10.455 --> 22:12.662
[Foghorn blows]

22:12.790 --> 22:15.372
I can't.
The foghorn is distracting me.

22:16.503 --> 22:21.042
Wait a minute.
I don't hear any foghorn.

22:23.384 --> 22:24.669
What does that mean?

22:29.724 --> 22:31.589
Carmen Brock, police!

22:32.060 --> 22:33.550
Carmen left the brambles
an hour ago.

22:33.686 --> 22:35.222
I'll call for a search warrant.

22:35.355 --> 22:37.061
Well, let me know when you get it.

22:42.987 --> 22:44.693
Carmen!

22:47.784 --> 22:49.615
She's not here.

22:52.539 --> 22:54.404
Why put the baby
in the living room?

22:55.291 --> 22:57.452
And no diaper pail.

22:58.253 --> 23:01.165
No baby—food splatter.

23:04.634 --> 23:06.499
I don't think they have
an actual baby.

23:06.636 --> 23:08.672
Then what's all this stuff for?

23:08.805 --> 23:10.341
The power of positive thinking?

23:10.473 --> 23:12.134
They want one.

23:14.018 --> 23:16.851
And look at this.
They've been trying |.V.F. for years.

23:17.647 --> 23:20.263
Carmen? Honey?

23:21.109 --> 23:22.269
Braer Brock?

23:22.402 --> 23:23.858
We're looking for your wife.

23:23.987 --> 23:25.727
So am |.
She's not answering her phone.

23:25.863 --> 23:26.727
What's going on?

23:26.864 --> 23:28.479
You heard
about the missing children?

23:28.616 --> 23:29.992
Of course.
Ben's my nephew.

23:30.118 --> 23:31.358
What's that got to do with Carmen?

23:31.494 --> 23:33.735
Your wife knows all three children.

23:33.871 --> 23:35.702
We think she has a trouble.

23:35.832 --> 23:36.912
Do you know what that means?

23:37.041 --> 23:39.202
Yes, but I can't believe
Carmen's troubled.

23:39.335 --> 23:41.041
And even if she was,
she wouldn't harm a child.

23:41.170 --> 23:42.376
She loves children.

23:42.505 --> 23:46.043
But you don't have any of your own,
despite a lot of trying.

23:46.175 --> 23:48.040
Did something happen recently?

23:48.177 --> 23:51.886
Something that upset her,
maybe a failed |.V.F. attempt?

23:52.015 --> 23:55.223
No, as you can see,
we're used to those.

23:56.352 --> 24:01.221
But, yes, Carmen's sister Valerie,
Ben's mom,

24:01.357 --> 24:04.690
she told us recently
that she's pregnant ——

24:04.819 --> 24:06.525
by accident.

24:07.363 --> 24:08.773
That she could conceive
without trying

24:08.906 --> 24:11.033
while we try and try,

24:11.159 --> 24:12.899
and all we have to show for it
is a mountain of debt

24:13.036 --> 24:16.779
and a pile of baby crap
collecting dust in the corner...

24:16.914 --> 24:18.120
That triggered her trouble.

24:18.249 --> 24:20.080
Carmen has created some creatures

24:20.209 --> 24:22.040
who've taken Kent
and Ben and Harper.

24:22.170 --> 24:23.956
And if we don't find them soon,
they're gonna die.

24:24.088 --> 24:25.919
Those are her three
favorite children.

24:26.049 --> 24:28.415
Well, maybe because
she can't have kids,

24:28.551 --> 24:30.792
her trouble is trying
to deprive others of theirs.

24:30.928 --> 24:31.917
No, you're wrong!

24:32.055 --> 24:32.965
I mean, if she's not here,

24:33.097 --> 24:35.474
it's 'cause she's gonna find
those kids.

24:35.600 --> 24:38.057
And that's it.
She's gonna bring them home.

24:40.480 --> 24:42.220
J” Ring around the Rosie J”

24:42.357 --> 24:44.393
J” A pocket full of posies J”

24:44.525 --> 24:46.516
J” Ashes, ashes J”

24:46.653 --> 24:50.612
J” We all fall down J”

24:50.740 --> 24:52.901
[Giggling]

24:56.204 --> 24:57.410
Harper.

25:01.751 --> 25:04.163
Harper.

25:04.295 --> 25:06.752
Oh, my God.
You're so cold.

25:08.549 --> 25:09.925
Oh, my God.

25:10.051 --> 25:11.837
It's cold.

25:11.969 --> 25:14.756
I want my mommy.

25:15.473 --> 25:16.303
Oh, my God.

25:16.432 --> 25:18.639
—I want to go home.
—I got to get you guys home.

25:18.768 --> 25:20.178
Come on, come on.

25:20.311 --> 25:22.302
[Child giggling]

25:35.493 --> 25:37.984
Harper, do you want to rest?

25:38.121 --> 25:40.954
Okay, you rest.

25:42.583 --> 25:44.323
Let's play!

25:44.460 --> 25:45.290
Come on.

25:46.421 --> 25:48.457
J” Ring around the Rosie J”

25:48.589 --> 25:50.841
J” A pocket full of posies J”

25:50.967 --> 25:52.252
J” Ashes... J”

25:57.056 --> 26:00.014
That's a child...with claws?

26:00.143 --> 26:02.680
A Douen. Probably took her
to meet with her kids.

26:02.812 --> 26:04.177
Troubles work on emotions,

26:04.313 --> 26:06.850
so it's likely a place your wife
feels her baby envy deepest.

26:06.983 --> 26:08.939
Carmen would never harm a child!

26:11.070 --> 26:13.152
She was built to be a mother, okay?

26:13.823 --> 26:15.984
Okay, maybe she isn't harming them.

26:16.784 --> 26:20.072
Maybe the Douens are assembling
a family for her.

26:20.663 --> 26:22.824
That's got to be it.

26:22.957 --> 26:24.788
Where would Carmen
be happiest with kids?

26:26.294 --> 26:29.161
There's a clearing
in the Chatham Woods

26:29.297 --> 26:30.457
where I proposed to her.

26:30.590 --> 26:32.546
All right, we'll follow you.

26:32.675 --> 26:34.211
[Cell phone beeping]

26:34.343 --> 26:35.674
What made you
switch theories so quick?

26:35.803 --> 26:36.713
Call it a hunch.

26:39.015 --> 26:40.880
Duke, what's Jennifer heard?

26:41.017 --> 26:42.507
—Lots of good stuff.
—We have to find a ——

26:44.145 --> 26:45.385
Duke, are you there?

26:45.521 --> 26:48.433
Yeah, could you just hang on
a second, please?

26:48.566 --> 26:50.352
—You've met Nathan.
—Yeah.

26:50.485 --> 26:51.600
Now, do you think
we really want him to know

26:51.736 --> 26:53.442
that if we don't find the door
then Audrey dies?

26:53.571 --> 26:55.937
—Probably not.
—Probably not.

26:56.073 --> 26:57.938
Nathan, find the kids.
We're doing great.

26:58.075 --> 26:59.531
Okay, I'll call you back.

26:59.660 --> 27:01.196
[Siren wails]

27:03.456 --> 27:04.787
We're doing great.

27:04.916 --> 27:05.621
[Cell phone beeps]

27:05.750 --> 27:07.411
Son of a bitch.

27:07.543 --> 27:08.658
The foghorn!

27:08.795 --> 27:10.376
—What?
—The foghorn.

27:10.505 --> 27:12.746
I thought I couldn't hear it
because I'm used to them.

27:12.882 --> 27:14.167
But what if only you can hear it

27:14.300 --> 27:15.801
because it's coming
through the barn?

27:15.927 --> 27:18.259
Why would the barn play a foghorn?

27:18.387 --> 27:19.092
No,no,no,no,no,no,no.

27:19.222 --> 27:20.962
Not from the barn,
through the barn.

27:21.098 --> 27:25.137
Look, I'm saying the barn is located
near a real—world foghorn.

27:25.269 --> 27:27.134
Okay, just now
I could hear a police siren

27:27.271 --> 27:28.556
coming through Nathan's phone.

27:28.689 --> 27:31.271
One way to find Nathan
would be to find the actual siren.

27:31.400 --> 27:33.265
Find the foghorn, find the door.

27:33.402 --> 27:35.814
—Find the foghorn, find the door.
—Great.

27:35.947 --> 27:36.777
How?

27:36.906 --> 27:39.443
I need my charts.

27:41.244 --> 27:42.279
Charts!

27:42.411 --> 27:45.403
[Foghorn blows]

27:46.916 --> 27:51.626
Listen to the foghorn,
and remember.

27:51.754 --> 27:54.245
It will help you find the door.

28:01.639 --> 28:04.551
It's coming from over here.

28:17.947 --> 28:20.063
lts here.

28:37.592 --> 28:38.832
[Gasps]

28:40.094 --> 28:41.755
Well done.

28:41.888 --> 28:43.844
All right, now what?

28:46.475 --> 28:48.011
—Open it.
—Open it?

28:48.144 --> 28:51.477
—Mm—hmm.
—All right.

28:59.822 --> 29:03.235
[Door opening]

29:05.661 --> 29:06.912
Now...

29:07.038 --> 29:08.778
What? What is it?

29:09.916 --> 29:12.453
—I think she opened her door.
—Not already!

29:25.848 --> 29:28.055
J” Ring around the Rosie J”

29:28.184 --> 29:30.266
J” A pocket full of posies J”

29:30.394 --> 29:32.555
J” Ashes, ashes J”

29:32.688 --> 29:37.102
J” We all fall... J”

29:37.234 --> 29:39.020
J” Down! J”

29:39.153 --> 29:41.394
[Children giggling]

29:44.367 --> 29:46.278
Leave her alone.
She's resting!

29:46.410 --> 29:47.570
lt's severe hypothermia.

29:47.703 --> 29:49.910
She'll die if we don't get her
to a hospital.

29:50.039 --> 29:50.949
[Growling]

29:51.082 --> 29:53.118
Ah!

29:53.250 --> 29:56.242
[Growling]

29:58.089 --> 30:00.330
Nathan, get Kent!

30:01.550 --> 30:04.166
[All growling, snarling]

30:06.472 --> 30:07.882
—What are you doing?
—They're too fast to hit.

30:08.015 --> 30:09.300
Those claws can sever arteries.

30:09.433 --> 30:10.764
We can't save those kids
if we're dead.

30:10.893 --> 30:12.804
What do we do now?

30:17.108 --> 30:18.439
You lied to me.

30:18.567 --> 30:21.104
There's nothing through there.
That goes nowhere.

30:21.237 --> 30:23.853
What you're seeing is
a barrier between two worlds.

30:23.990 --> 30:26.322
It's not a space that you can inhabit,
but it's not endless.

30:26.450 --> 30:27.610
You can cross it.

30:27.743 --> 30:29.529
What?
No. No way.

30:29.662 --> 30:31.118
—Uh—uh.
—You can do this.

30:31.247 --> 30:32.862
How am I supposed to do that?

30:34.125 --> 30:35.990
You make a leap of faith.

30:40.256 --> 30:42.918
[Growling, snarling]

30:48.014 --> 30:50.551
My wife ——
This trouble has made her crazy.

30:50.683 --> 30:53.140
Did you notice
the Douens didn't attack you?

30:53.269 --> 30:55.601
This isn't Carmen's trouble, Braer.

30:55.730 --> 30:57.186
It's yours.

30:58.107 --> 31:00.063
They didn't attack you
because you created them.

31:00.192 --> 31:01.477
That's absurd.

31:01.610 --> 31:03.396
Carmen's playing
the protective mother

31:03.529 --> 31:05.895
because she's under their spell,
which is just what you want.

31:06.032 --> 31:07.897
I don't want any of this.

31:08.034 --> 31:10.946
You promised her a family

31:11.078 --> 31:14.411
when you proposed to her
right here on this spot.

31:14.540 --> 31:18.249
That's the fantasy the Douens
are carrying out for you.

31:18.377 --> 31:20.663
lt's Carmen who can't accept
being childless.

31:20.796 --> 31:21.660
l've accepted it.

31:21.797 --> 31:25.255
But you haven't accepted the fact
that it's your fault.

31:27.136 --> 31:29.593
|.V.F. files say
there's nothing wrong with Carmen.

31:29.722 --> 31:30.962
Those tests could have been wrong!

31:31.098 --> 31:33.840
Look, | get it.

31:33.976 --> 31:38.515
You're married to a woman
who's built to have children,

31:38.647 --> 31:40.603
but she can't have them.

31:41.192 --> 31:43.148
I lost a son.

31:43.944 --> 31:47.107
I might even be responsible
for his death.

31:47.239 --> 31:50.572
But denying that it's my fault
doesn't help.

31:51.243 --> 31:52.494
All I can do is move on.

31:52.620 --> 31:55.828
You got to do the same
or those kids are gonna die.

31:58.167 --> 32:00.032
Nathan.

32:06.008 --> 32:07.748
Please.

32:07.885 --> 32:10.547
You have to face the truth.

32:13.224 --> 32:15.180
It's my fault.

32:17.144 --> 32:19.521
[Crying]
It's my fault.

32:22.358 --> 32:24.019
[Children giggling]

32:33.702 --> 32:34.862
Hey, hey.

32:34.995 --> 32:35.745
What happened?

32:35.871 --> 32:38.078
Your husband just decided
it's time to adopt.

32:38.874 --> 32:40.739
You're gonna be okay.

32:40.876 --> 32:42.537
[Sobbing]

32:46.048 --> 32:48.130
Do we know if my friends
have opened up their door

32:48.259 --> 32:49.999
on the other side?

32:50.803 --> 32:52.043
I don't know.

32:52.179 --> 32:53.214
You want me to jump,

32:53.347 --> 32:55.463
and we don't even know
if I'm gonna live or die?

32:55.599 --> 32:58.841
I guess that's why they call it
a leap of faith.

33:08.612 --> 33:11.945
It's not his fault, really.
It's a biological problem.

33:12.074 --> 33:15.362
Braer didn't see it that way,
and I can see why.

33:15.494 --> 33:17.906
Is it my fault that my daughter
inherited my trouble?

33:18.038 --> 33:21.872
Probably not,
but I blame myself for her death.

33:22.001 --> 33:22.990
If you knew it was his trouble,

33:23.127 --> 33:24.833
why didn't you talk him
down back at the house?

33:24.962 --> 33:28.125
We had missing kids.
I didn't want to stop for anything.

33:30.050 --> 33:31.551
I got to go.

33:31.677 --> 33:33.884
Good luck.

33:34.305 --> 33:37.923
[Cell phone beeping,
line trilling]

33:38.642 --> 33:40.928
-Yeah?
—Duke, did you find anything?

33:41.061 --> 33:42.141
Yeah.

33:42.271 --> 33:45.604
l-l would say yes, we did.

33:45.733 --> 33:48.145
Just get down here.

33:52.990 --> 33:54.821
Nathan's on his way.

33:55.284 --> 33:56.865
And I'm still not seeing the door.

33:56.994 --> 33:59.906
Tell me I didn't just lie to him.

34:00.039 --> 34:01.904
It's right here, Duke.
l'm staring right at it.

34:02.666 --> 34:03.781
Is it open?

34:03.918 --> 34:05.749
lt's closed.

34:05.878 --> 34:07.789
If we don't open it,
Audrey dies.

34:08.422 --> 34:10.879
I know. I'm trying.
It won't budge.

34:14.011 --> 34:16.093
DUKE: Nathan's gonna hate this.

34:23.187 --> 34:25.098
[Grunts]

34:25.231 --> 34:26.562
NATHAN:
Pull harder or something.

34:27.316 --> 34:29.227
It won't open, Nathan.

34:29.818 --> 34:31.979
I think because Audrey
closed her door on her side again.

34:32.112 --> 34:33.613
What do you mean
she closed her door?

34:33.739 --> 34:35.024
What, did she change her mind?
Is she not coming?

34:35.157 --> 34:36.488
I don't know!
Stop yelling at me.

34:36.617 --> 34:37.732
Nathan, that's enough.

34:37.868 --> 34:39.244
Look, we found the door, okay?

34:39.370 --> 34:40.985
She's gonna come out any minute.
We just ——

34:43.165 --> 34:46.373
How the hell did they find us?

34:46.502 --> 34:49.960
We followed you, Nathan,
in case you got cold feet.

34:50.631 --> 34:53.213
—Give me your gun.
—No way.

34:53.342 --> 34:54.457
Nathan, don't do this.

34:54.593 --> 34:56.129
You don't get a say in this, Crocker.

34:56.262 --> 34:57.718
—You shut up. Nathan.
—He made a deal.

34:59.348 --> 35:00.884
Nathan, listen to me.

35:01.350 --> 35:02.965
Duke”.

35:03.102 --> 35:05.935
Let him go.
We're doing this.

35:06.063 --> 35:08.179
I'm doing this.

35:14.530 --> 35:17.772
—Thanks.
—AUDREY: Leap of faith.

35:18.534 --> 35:21.446
Leap of faith. Right.

35:27.543 --> 35:29.534
She's opening her door.

35:31.839 --> 35:32.919
Okay.

35:33.048 --> 35:35.505
Okay, all right.

35:56.405 --> 35:58.191
I can't open it.

35:59.742 --> 36:01.983
Maybe it has to be me.

36:07.791 --> 36:10.407
No one's opening that door!

36:11.920 --> 36:15.003
We have to open it,
or Audrey will die.

36:15.132 --> 36:16.668
Dave, put the gun down.

36:16.800 --> 36:17.585
I tried to stop him,

36:17.718 --> 36:19.333
but he's got some crazy notion
in his head

36:19.470 --> 36:20.550
from reading the archives.

36:20.679 --> 36:22.635
It's not crazy.

36:22.765 --> 36:26.474
Opening that door could unleash
powers far beyond our control.

36:33.442 --> 36:35.398
So you, um...

36:36.445 --> 36:37.776
You want to go first?

36:38.280 --> 36:39.781
I'm not coming.

36:40.282 --> 36:41.271
Why not?

36:41.408 --> 36:44.650
This is a journey
only you can make.

36:44.787 --> 36:47.403
Don't worry.
We'll all be fine.

36:47.539 --> 36:49.495
And I'm sure we'll meet again.

36:49.625 --> 36:51.866
I hope so.

36:56.673 --> 36:58.755
We have to open it,
or Audrey dies.

36:58.884 --> 37:00.670
I know, Nathan.
I'm sorry.

37:00.803 --> 37:04.216
But I —— I promise you,
it's a small price to pay ——

37:04.348 --> 37:06.464
[ Electricity crackles]

37:08.143 --> 37:09.974
When Audrey comes out,
I'll start throwing punches,

37:10.104 --> 37:11.093
give you guys a head start.

37:12.106 --> 37:14.313
No. The troubles end now.

37:14.441 --> 37:16.306
Go on.

37:47.015 --> 37:50.303
You know, you kept saying
that I'm not who I think I am.

37:51.478 --> 37:53.890
If I make it to the other side...

37:54.565 --> 37:56.271
...who will I be?

37:56.900 --> 37:59.767
Whoever you most want to be.

38:01.321 --> 38:03.061
Audrey!

38:03.198 --> 38:04.734
Audrey!

38:41.278 --> 38:42.734
No.

39:18.273 --> 39:19.524
Audrey.

39:20.317 --> 39:21.978
Audrey.

39:22.110 --> 39:23.771
Hey.

39:52.808 --> 39:54.639
You made it.

39:55.477 --> 39:57.433
Hi.

39:58.355 --> 40:00.437
Hi.

40:32.014 --> 40:33.879
What are you doing?

40:34.016 --> 40:35.802
The troubles haven't ended.

40:35.934 --> 40:38.676
I know what Howard told you.

40:38.812 --> 40:40.348
Killing me is the only way now.

41:09.343 --> 41:11.459
Please.

41:11.595 --> 41:13.836
Please, Audrey.

41:23.440 --> 41:25.726
I'm not killing anyone.

41:27.069 --> 41:29.981
Certainly not someone
I've never met before.

41:32.532 --> 41:34.068
What?

41:37.079 --> 41:39.115
And who is Audrey?

41:40.332 --> 41:43.199
My name is Lexie.
